Jones won 11-5 in a one-sided final to take gold having previously earned two bronze medals and one silver in the continental event.
A quick start gave the Welsh athlete a three-point advantage and a trademark head shot early in the second doubled her lead and effectively sealed the contest against one of her chief rivals for the Olympic crown.
Bianca Walkden and Mahama Cho have also secured their places at this summer's Olympic Games. The final place will go to either Lutalo Muhammad and Damon Sansum.
